cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Historical Entity Tracker"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Pedahzur
    given-names: Ami
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0925-4993"
    affiliation: "University of Haifa"
repository-code: "https://github.com/pedahzur/historical-entity-tracker"
abstract: >-
  A tool for tracing people, organizations, places, and events across a
  multilingual historical corpus to support relative causality analysis.
  LLM structured outputs extract entities and events grounded in exact
  source quotes; cross-document and cross-language resolution proposes
  confidence-scored links; a historian adjudicates every link in a
  review workspace. Co-presence is treated as a hypothesis, not a fact.
keywords:
  - named entity recognition
  - entity resolution
  - historical methods
  - multilingual corpora
  - large language models
  - computational social science
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-09
